A high demand for medical technology in Asia has driven sales of Carl Zeiss Meditec.
In the first nine months of the financial year which began in October, the Group's turnover increased by 6.7 percent to EUR 798.6 million, the listed company said on Friday in Jena.
Asian business grew disproportionately by 17.1 percent.
The profit before interest and taxes increased from EUR 89.5 million to EUR 110.5 million according to the interim balance sheet.
The medical technology group in Jena intends to exceed the turnover mark of one billion euros this financial year, the Management Board confirmed.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures equipment and equipment for medical practices and clinics.
